---
title: Teriyaki Chicken Stir-Fry with Snow Peas over White Rice
description: Simple and speedy is the name of the game here with our ready-to-go teriyaki sauce, precut chicken strips, and microwavable rice. After only a few minutes of tossing the meat and snow peas in a pan, simply pour in the sauce and you’re good to go. Just don’t forget the sesame garnish, which opens the door to sensational and savory stir-fry magic.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/teriyaki-chicken-stir-fry-4502f6ac.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/teriyaki-chicken-stir-fry-5ac788dfae08b57c03654242-46e73af9.pdf
author: HelloFresh
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 760 kcal
  fat: 24 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 64 g
  sugar: 20 g
  protein: 72 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1120 mg
cuisine: Japanese
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/teriyaki-chicken-stir-fry-5ac788dfae08b57c03654242
---

Wash and dry all produce. Halve and peel @yellow onion{2}, then cut into ½-inch-thick wedges. Pat @chicken breast strips{20%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a #small pan{} over medium heat. Add @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} and toast, stirring a few times, until fragrant and golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Heat @olive oil{2%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add chicken and cook, tossing occasionally, until browned on surface, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add onion to pan and cook, tossing occasionally, until starting to brown, about ~{3%minutes}. Toss in @snow peas{16%ounce} and cook until tender but still a little crisp, about ~{2%minutes}.

Pour @teriyaki sauce{8%ounce} into pan and bring to a simmer. Let bubble until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Heat @microwavable jasmine rice{2%pack} according to package directions, then place in a #large bowl{} and fluff with a #fork{}. Stir in @butter{2%tablespoon} and half the sesame seeds. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between plates and arrange chicken stir-fry on top. Sprinkle with remaining sesame seeds and serve.

> Simple and speedy is the name of the game here with our ready-to-go teriyaki sauce, precut
> chicken strips, and microwavable rice. The sesame garnish opens the door to sensational
> and savory stir-fry magic.